                <h2>[k means analogy - 1 column, 1 or 2 paragraphs]</h2>
                <p>Lets forget for a moment that computers and the web exists. Say you are at a fundraising event where 50,000 projects are looking for backers and there are 200,000 people that are looking for projects to back. Currently, the situation is extremely chaotic. It is similar to being in a football stadium with 50,000 people that have projects and are looking for your funding. The editors choice panel on kickstarter is like having a few lucky people being broadcast on the jumbotron in the stadium. The new projects panel is like hanging out by the entrance and seeing the flood new projects coming in. Its a mess.</p>
                <p>What the Kickammender recommendation engine does is transform the stadium into a skyscraper. As you enter the lobby of the building, a receptionist analyses your interests and tells you to go to room 17 on the 62nd floor.</p>


             </div>
              <div class="col-sm-4">
